g.text: Individual income (or in some cases, consumption) inequality (Gini coefficient)
Selected countries highlighted. Green modelled line is 95% confidence interval of a mixed effects model with random country effect.
Higher inequality countries have more homicides. But modelling choices impact on 'how much'.
Source: World Bank, World Development Indicators, series VC.IHR.PSRC.P5 and SI.POV.GINI. Analysis by freerangestats.info.
